===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# To make safe; to relieve from apprehensions of, or exposure to, danger; to guard; to protect.
#* {{RQ:Dryden Aeneis}}
#*: I spread a cloud before the victor's sight, / Sustained the vanquished, and '''secured''' his flight.
# To put beyond hazard of losing or of not receiving; to make certain; to assure; frequently with ''against'' or ''from'', or formerly with ''of''.
#: ''to '''secure''' a creditor against loss; to '''secure''' a debt by a mortgage''
#* '''1831''', {{w|Thomas Dick (scientist)|Thomas Dick}}, ''The Philosophy of Religion''
#*: It '''secures''' its possessor of eternal happiness.
# To make fast; to close or confine effectually; to render incapable of getting loose or escaping.
#: ''to '''secure''' a prisoner; to '''secure''' a door, or the hatches of a ship''
# To get possession of; to make oneself secure of; to acquire certainly.
#: ''to '''secure''' an estate''
#* '''2014''', Jamie Jackson, "[http://www.theguardian.com/football/2014/aug/26/angel-di-maria-completes-move-to-manchester-united Ángel di María says Manchester United were the ‘only club’ after Real]", ''The Guardian'', 26 August 2014:
#*: With the Argentinian '''secured''' United will step up their attempt to sign a midfielder and, possibly, a defender in the closing days of the transfer window. Juventus’s Arturo Vidal, Milan’s Nigel de Jong and Ajax’s Daley Blind, who is also a left-sided defensive player, are potential targets.
#* {{quote-journal|en| passage=[Captain] was able to secure some good photographs of the fortress.| pageurl=http://www.flightglobal.com/pdfarchive/view/1911/1911%20-%200764.html| journal=Flight| year=1911| page=766}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1918|author={{w|W. B. Maxwell}}|chapter=3| title=[http://openlibrary.org/works/OL1097634W The Mirror and the Lamp]| passage=One saint's day in mid-term a certain newly appointed suffragan-bishop came to the school chapel, and there preached on “The Inner Life.” He at once '''secured''' attention by his informal method, and when presently the coughing of Jarvis {{...}} interrupted the sermon, he altogether captivated his audience with a remark about cough lozenges being cheap and easily procurable.}}
